messages:
Name: Youssef En-Nesyri
Nationality: Morocco
Date of Birth: June 1, 1997
Position: Attacker
Current club: Sevilla
LaLiga clubs played for: Málaga, Leganés, Sevilla

Youssef En-Nesyri, the Sevilla attacker, has played in the vast majority of their LaLiga matches in 2023/2024, making 33 appearances overall and accumulating 2,576 minutes of playing time. He has started in 28 of these appearances across their 38 fixtures and been used as a substitute on five occasions.

En-Nesyri last played in the league on May 26 for Sevilla against Barcelona. In that match the Moroccan player scored for his side in their 2-1 loss. The attacker is ranked joint sixth in the LaLiga goalscoring charts with a tally of 16 goals this campaign, as well as being the team's top league scorer. En-Nesyri has also provided two assists as well. He has been shown four yellow cards.
It was versus Valencia that En-Nesyri scored for the first time in the league this season in a 2-1 loss on August 11.
Last season for Sevilla, En-Nesyri made 31 Primera División appearances, scored eight goals and provided one assist.
Before moving to Sevilla in January 2020, En-Nesyri made 49 league appearances in total at Leganés, scoring 13 goals and providing four assists.

En-Nesyri started his LaLiga career for Málaga on August 26, 2016, playing 13 minutes as a substitute against Espanyol at the age of 19 years and 86 days. He debuted at LaLiga level for current team Sevilla in their encounter against Real Madrid on January 18, 2020.
In his LaLiga career overall, he has played 230 games in the competition, with 69 goals scored and nine assists. En-Nesyri has also been sent off once, with 24 yellow cards collected overall.
